entity.event

Class Event

  • java.lang.Object
    • entity.Identifiable
      • entity.event.Event
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IEvent, java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Talk

    public abstract class Event
extends Identifiable
implements IEvent
    An Event is a subclass of IEvent meaning it occupies a time and location for an Schedule, specifically, an Event can only be added to Schedule of the conference. This way when the organizer plans the event, there won't be double booking of the time or location, this is enforced in Schedule.
